********** BEST PRACTICES FOR WRITING PYTHON CODE ( ANY PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE )
#variables 
1.snake_case
2.start with lowercase or underscore 
3.letters numbers and underscore 
4.case sernsitve 
4.constants are declared in the capital lettres . the values should never change
5.dunder variables is with two underscores . don't create a variables with two underscores .




************************8
 functions and types of arguments and parameters 
 
#parameters
#default parameters 

def say_hello(name='shoe',emoji="**"):
    print("hello: "+name + " expression: "+emoji)
    
   
#arguments
say_hello('ramya',":)")


#positional arguments 
say_hello("andrei","&!")

#keyword arguments 
#make sure to put it in order to avoid confusion 

say_hello(emoji= ":(", name="listing") 
say_hello() #will give you the default arguments
